HEADWORD: jazzy
<hw>jazzy</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>resembling jazz{1}
especially in its rhythm.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>ostentatious or strikingly styled; -- used
especially of clothes.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flashy, gaudy, showy, snazzy, sporty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>marked by animation or performed with
flair[2].</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

